        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Actually, I think it can be done.  Here's my idea on this.  Sleeper has got an immense ammount of HP's, anyone who says they know for sure is most likely full of it.  Anyways, I would say with the bane weapons out there, perhaps there's something that has a dragon bane, not sure, don't play melees anymore.  If not, no biggie.</P><P>Would have to be done in waves.  Key to it being keep the sleeper in the tomb.  First wave goes in buffed and begins the fight with one cleric per group.  Pet classes, don't matter how useless they are, send them in.  Necros assisting healers by healing/mana dumping.  Chanters chain stunning dunno, but fear keeps CT from using his DT as does chain stun/mez (chanters do get stun, or am I smoking too much crack again?), may work here.  As the first wave hit's about 50% left, 2nd wave goes in.  Same scenario.  Battle clerics are a must, and probably all clerics will be.  Necros with clicky corpse robes pull dead out of the fight's way, and battle clerics chain rez.  If necessary, 3rd wave goes in to buy some more time.  Basicaly, Zerg her punk ass to death.  I would say melees using high damage weapons as they will probably not get in more than 4 or 5 swings before they all start falling.  Disease dots would probably work, being the sleeper is, if I remember the backstory correctly, the child of vox and naggy but fire and cold will probably not.</P><P>If nothing else, dire charm Yalenak and see how he does.  LOL</P><P>Kinda makes you hope we do get that anti regen spell, no?</P><P>BTW, I am well aware that is basic tactics, but you gotta start somewhere.</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=311916" target="_blank">Lizalfos Deathscale</a><BR><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
