         Actually Vel, Tiamat was a pagan goddess, the one of chaos.  She was killed and her blood became the waters, her breath the air, her bone the ground, and her flesh life.  She's more than just a D&D thing.  Just thought I would throw in some culture there, sorry.</P><P>On the sleeper, I think the fight would have to take place in the tomb itself.  The ley is to not let her get any self helping abilities on her.  Has anyone been present during her awakening who knows if dispells did anything to her perhaps she spawns with some buffs on her, or buffs herself just before she comes out.  I don't know, wasn't there when she was awoken in TM.  As someone mentioned the sleeper may be part of a quest.  Since I am not aware of any server that hasn't awakened her, I can only say we will never know unless Verant decides to respawn her in the sleeper form.  However, unless there is special coding on her, the sleeper does have to exist in the game somewhere because there has been no confirmed respawn.  Perhaps we will get another shot in the PoP expansion, possible for her to be in PoA, and is triggered as the result of a quest there.  Could be a broodmother type quest where the dragons gather in WL or WW, once again, possibly PoA there too.</P><P>The key is to find something that will hurt her (dragon bane weapons), or find the quest to do it.  I would imagine all the named dragons (in velious) beating on her would do something if done all at the same time.  Possible DT resists?  doubtful but if possible would require a huge ammount of MR I would think.</P><P>Perhaps there's a faction she's on that you can get on yourself and she is just a quest NPC, and considered to be Verants first try at invincable mobs, like the nexus scions.</P><P>I dunno, just rambling...</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=311916" target="_blank">Lizalfos Deathscale</a><BR><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go t